values:
So I am in my second week of work, and I am liking it so far.&nbsp; I'm not doing too much actual work - as you can tell from the three posts in a row today :)&nbsp;but that will all change next week when the Senior Pastor (who I am actually working for) is back.&nbsp; He's been in Australia the last two weeks, and gets back to the states Saturday.&nbsp; I am getting settled - have some decorations in my office&nbsp;(but most still need to be hung up) and am learning the people and the systems.&nbsp; Today there is a labyrinth set up, so I'm looking forward to taking some time to walk it.

Josh and I are going to RENT at the Fox Theatre Saturday evening and are way super excited about it.&nbsp; We saw it in Cleveland - but we have super close seats this time.&nbsp; I cannot wait.&nbsp; I'm getting settled into Atlanta life, and am loving it more and more each day.&nbsp; Now if I could only get Josh down here - it wouldn't feel so much like a vacation and would actually feel like a new life.&nbsp; Patience grasshopper.

The&nbsp;internet at my apartment has not been working lately.&nbsp; I've been told it's the wi-fi from the Atlanta Fish Market, and probably the whole neighborhood uses it, so I haven't had much time at home on the net - sad face.&nbsp; Luckily, my job hasn't been crazy busy so I don't feel internet-deprived yet :)&nbsp;
